Hi guys! I have a dynamic page based on crm, where one of the custom properties in the crm object is a rich text editor. I've tried rendering this RTE content as is, with the inline styles the editor has added, but its always just pure <p> in the rendering.

Ive tried
{{ campaign.campaign_cars___introduction_text }}
{{ campaign.campaign_cars___introduction_text | raw }}
{{ campaign.campaign_cars___introduction_text | html }}
{{ campaign.campaign_cars___introduction_text | safe }}
{% inline_rich_text field="richtext_field" value="{{campaign.campaign_cars___introduction_text}}" %}

most doesnt work, pprint gives
(String: <p><span>this is <strong>bold</strong>. </span>
<span>Smaller text, fontsize 8.</span></p>)

which means im not even getting the font size adjustments but i am getting <strong>

Hi Folks,
i use a select dropdown in my hubdb, when i try to do display the selected option i get an object output of the whole table, what am i doing wrong, probably need to loop trough the {{row.function}} ?

```
   &lt;div class="card-collection-container"&gt;
     {% for row in hubdb_table_rows( module.hubdbtable_field ) %}
     &lt;div class="card-container"&gt;
      &lt;a class="card-item-link" href="#"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;div class="card-collection-content"&gt;
        &lt;h5 style="margin:0;"&gt;{{row.headline}}&lt;/h5&gt;
        &lt;a class="card-collection-category-container"&gt;&lt;img class="card-collection-category-icon"&gt;
         &lt;div class="card-collection-category"&gt;{{row.function}}&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;p style="margin:0;" class="card-collection-body"&gt;{{row.description}}&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;img class="card-collection-background" src={{row.thumbnail.url}}&gt;
     &lt;/div&gt;
     {% endfor %}
  &lt;/div&gt;```
